                    <comment id="12862530" author="shaie" created="Fri, 30 Apr 2010 05:23:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Mike - this patch is against an old revision? I&apos;m up to the latest and IndexInput/Output don&apos;t include any field, just abstract methods. This seems to be relevant to 3.0.1 (and before?) If so, where does this need to be fixed post 3.0.1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12862606" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 30 Apr 2010 10:30:39 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mike - this patch is against an old revision? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, sorry, the patch applies to 2.9.x.  I think we should fix it in 2.9.x (and all branches after &amp;#8211; 3.0, trunk).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In trunk these reused byte[] have been moved to DataInput/Output.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
